
# Ref: https://medium.com/@cibofdevs/complete-guide-to-crud-using-mybatis-and-spring-boot-d6c165167cdd

PRE-REQUISITES (ORACLE):

-- Basic CRUD
-- Non identity column
CREATE TABLE ADWH.EMPLOYEE (
    ID          NUMBER      PRIMARY KEY,
    NAME        VARCHAR2(100)   NOT NULL,
    DEPARTMENT  VARCHAR2(100)   NOT NULL
);

-- Identity column
CREATE TABLE ADWH.EMPLOYEE (
    ID NUMBER GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
    NAME        VARCHAR2(100)   NOT NULL,
    DEPARTMENT  VARCHAR2(100)   NOT NULL
);

-- Helper
INSERT INTO ADWH.EMPLOYEE (NAME, DEPARTMENT) VALUES ('John Doe', 'Data Management');
SELECT * FROM ADWH.EMPLOYEE;
UPDATE ADWH.EMPLOYEE SET DEPARTMENT = 'LOREM' WHERE ID = 1;
TRUNCATE TABLE ADWH.EMPLOYEE;

-- Transaction
DROP TABLE ADWH.BOOKINGS;
CREATE TABLE ADWH.BOOKINGS (
	ID NUMBER GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
	FIRST_NAME VARCHAR2(5) NOT NULL
);

TRUNCATE TABLE ADWH.BOOKINGS;
SELECT * FROM ADWH.BOOKINGS;



# Start the Spring Boot Application #

A. From IntelliJ:
    1. Open the project.
    2. Open DemoApplication.java
    3. Click the green â–¶ Run button.

B. from terminal:
    1. mvn spring-boot:run
    2. mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring.profiles.active=prod
    (working with environment)
    3. mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring.profiles.active=prod -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=prod
    3. mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring.profiles.active=dev -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=dev

C. If you built a jar:
    1. mvn clean package
    2. java -jar target/springboot-mybatis-oracle-demo-1.0.0.jar
    3. mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring.profiles.active=prod
    4. java -jar target/springboot-mybatis-oracle-demo-1.0.0.jar --spring.profiles.active=prod

The app starts on:
    http://localhost:8080